STRUCTURE | SPECIFICATIONS v4

ATLAS CONSTRUCTION PROJECT
Comprehensive Structural Design Specifications
Version: 4.0 | Date: 2026-03-04 | Classification: INTERNAL

====================================================================
SECTION 1: GENERAL REQUIREMENTS
====================================================================

1.1 DESIGN STANDARDS
- Australian Standards: AS 3600, AS 4100
- Building Code of Australia: NCC 2022
- Wind Code: AS/NZS 1170.2
- Seismic Code: AS/NZS 1170.4
- Design Life: 75 years

1.2 DESIGN LOADS
- Live Load (Office): 4.0 kPa
- Live Load (Retail): 5.0 kPa
- Wind Speed: 60 m/s (Ultimate)
- Seismic Zone: C (PGA = 0.3g)
- Environmental: Moderate exposure

1.3 SAFETY FACTORS
- Partial Factor on Materials: 1.5 (steel), 1.4 (concrete)
- Partial Factor on Actions: 1.6 (permanent), 1.5 (variable)
- Combined Factor of Safety: 3.0+ throughout

====================================================================
SECTION 2: CONCRETE DESIGN
====================================================================

2.1 CONCRETE GRADE
- Column Concrete: C50 (50 MPa @ 28 days)
- Slab Concrete: C40 (40 MPa @ 28 days)
- Pile Concrete: C50 (50 MPa @ 28 days)
- Slump: 120-150mm (all grades)

2.2 REINFORCEMENT
- Main Reinforcement: Grade 500 (fy = 500 MPa)
- Links/Stirrups: Grade 500
- Minimum Cover: 50mm (columns), 40mm (slabs)
- Lap Length: 50 Ø (Grade 500)

2.3 DURABILITY
- Carbonation Depth Limit: 10mm (75 years)
- Crack Width Limit: 0.2mm (reinforced), 0.15mm (PS)
- Chloride Ingress Protection: Grade C50 concrete mandatory

====================================================================
SECTION 3: STEEL DESIGN
====================================================================

3.1 STRUCTURAL STEEL
- Main Frames: S355 (fy = 355 MPa, fu = 510 MPa)
- Connections: S275 or higher
- Bolts: 8.8 grade high-strength bolts
- Welds: E7018 electrodes, FCAW for semi-automatic

3.2 COLUMN DESIGN
- Buckling Check: AS 4100 Section 5.6
- Slenderness Ratio: Max λ = 150
- Connection Moment Capacity: ≥ 75% beam capacity

3.3 BEAM DESIGN
- Flexural Capacity Check: φ Mn ≥ 1.6 Md
- Shear Capacity Check: φ Vn ≥ 1.5 Vd
- Deflection Limit: Span/250 (permanent loads)
- Composite Action: Shear studs @ 300mm spacing

====================================================================
SECTION 4: FOUNDATION DESIGN
====================================================================

4.1 PILE FOUNDATION
- Pile Type: Bored Cast-in-Place Reinforced Concrete
- Diameter: 1.2m (standard), 1.5m (corner piles)
- Design Capacity: 3,100 kN per pile (working load)
- Minimum Depth: 32m below formation level

4.2 BEARING CAPACITY
- Allowable Bearing Pressure: 1,500 kPa
- Subsidence: < 50mm total, < 20mm differential
- Settlement Analysis: Performed per Terzaghi methodology

4.3 PILE CAP DESIGN
- Grade Beams: C50 concrete
- Dimensions: 1.5m wide x 1.2m deep
- Reinforcement: Grade 500 @ 20mm spacing both faces

====================================================================
SECTION 5: COMPOSITE DESIGN
====================================================================

5.1 COMPOSITE DECKING
- Floor System: Composite (steel deck + concrete topping)
- Deck Profile: 150mm total depth
- Steel Deck: 75mm profiled (fastened to beams)
- Concrete Topping: 75mm C40, reinforced with mesh

5.2 SHEAR CONNECTION
- Shear Studs: ∅19mm x 95mm, Grade 8.8
- Spacing: 300mm along beams
- Capacity: 300 kN per stud (working load)
- Pattern: Staggered, 2 per flange width

====================================================================
SECTION 6: QUALITY CONTROL
====================================================================

6.1 CONCRETE TESTING
- Slump Test: Every 50 m³ or daily
- Compressive Strength: 3 no./test day (cylinders)
- 28-day Strength Verification: Mandatory
- Chloride Content Test: Annual on site samples

6.2 STEEL TESTING
- Mill Test Certificates: All deliveries
- Tensile Tests: Per AS 4100 requirements
- Hardness Testing: Fracture Critical welds (UT)
- Non-Destructive Testing: 10% of welded connections

6.3 TOLERANCES
- Dimensional: ±50mm for main elements
- Verticality: ±25mm in 10m height
- Levelness: ±10mm in 10m length
- Plumb: ±1:500 for column lines

